- `src/types.ts` — `User` interface (`id`, `name`, `email`, `role`) — no changes needed
- `src/routes.ts` — current `GET /users` handler is just `res.json(users)` (line 8) — **this is the only edit**
- `tests/routes.test.ts` — **all 4 pagination tests are already written** and waiting; just need the implementation to pass

### The change (full replacement of the handler body)

```typescript
router.get("/users", (req, res) => {
  const page       = Math.max(1, parseInt(req.query.page  as string, 10) || 1);
  const limit      = Math.max(1, parseInt(req.query.limit as string, 10) || 10);
  const total      = users.length;
  const totalPages = Math.ceil(total / limit);
  const offset     = (page - 1) * limit;
  const data       = users.slice(offset, offset + limit);

  res.json({ data, pagination: { page, limit, total, totalPages } });
});
```

### Key design notes
- `|| 1` / `|| 10` handles missing/NaN params → defaults
- `Math.max(1, ...)` guards against 0 or negative inputs
- `Array.slice` naturally returns `[]` when `offset >= total`, so out-of-range pages need no special-case branch
- `GET /users/:id` is completely untouched
- `npm test` should show all 6 tests green after the change
